    • Constructor Detail

      • CTLogInfo

        public CTLogInfo​(String url,
                 byte[] publicKeyBytes,
                 String label,
                 int timeout)
        Creates a CT log info object, but does not parse the public key yet (so it can be created from static blocks etc.)
        Parameters:
        url - Base URL to the log. The CT log library will automatically append the strings "add-chain" or "add-pre-chain" depending on whether EJBCA is submitting a pre-certificate or a regular certificate.
        publicKeyBytes - The ASN1 encoded public key of the log.
        label - to place CT log under.
        timeout - of SCT response in ms.

      • getExpirationYearRequired

        public Integer getExpirationYearRequired()
        Returns the expiration year which certificates published to this CT log must have in order to be accepted, or null if there is no such requirement. For example, if this method returns "2019" then you should only try to publish certificates to this CT log expiring in 2019, since all other certificates will be rejected.
        Returns:
        the expiration year required for all certificates being published to this log or null if there is no such requirement

      • setExpirationYearRequired

        public void setExpirationYearRequired​(Integer expirationYearRequired)
        Returns the expiration year which certificates published to this CT log must have in order to be accepted, or null if there is no such requirement. See getExpirationYearRequired().
        Parameters:
        expirationYearRequired - the expiration year required for new certificates being published to this CT log, or null if no such requirement
